The final words about a failed marriage usually belong to men. «If he decides that he’s going to divorce, I will let him» is how most women in the country justify measures. It’s possible that she harbours a hope that his intentions might change after making a decision. After all, even those who have made up their minds about ending a marriage often choose to procrastinate or just wait for «the right» (i.e. convenient) moment. It seems that most men in Kyrgyzstan share that attitude to divorce.

On your knees?

Often, it is the women who decide that they cannot make a marriage function any more and agree to divorce. In the case of the Hasanov family, the decision was made by the man. His experience is a perfect illustration of how things propagate in Kyrgyz society.

For a long time, Hasanov was not even sure that his wife had returned to her family. So it only gradually came to his mind that he had become a husband for the second (or was it his third?) time. Feeling a bit ashamed that he had become someone’s second choice, he still invited his new wife’s husband and son to their house and submitted himself to them at court. Very western, huh?
